==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Intermarry
<hw>In`ter*mar"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To become
connected by marriage between their members; to give and take mutually
in marriage; -- said of families, ranks, races, castes, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>About the middle of the fourth century from the building of Rome,
it was declared lawful for nobles and plebeians to
<qex>intermarry</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Swift.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Intermaxilla</ent>⟦br⟧
